name: Pescador
description:
I met this place, Chachín, on my way to Chile. I wanted to stay and see this place in the photo.

The man tried to fish under the sun for hours. But he came out of the water empty-handed. When he stepped on land, he greeted me. It was nice to have a brief conversation with him. There were few humans for miles around.

Horses, fish, cows and insects were our hosts.

Photograph taken near the Chachin Waterfall on Lake Nonthue.

02.27.2020
